    <div class="section">
      <p>This project was developed as part of the <strong>Python for Data Science</strong> module in my Postgraduate Program in Data Science. The objective was to analyze a dataset from an automobile company to uncover insights into customer demand and identify target demographics for various vehicle segments.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üîç Project Objectives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to understand customer behavior and market trends.</li>
        <li>Segment customers based on demographics such as age, income, and region.</li>
        <li>Identify high-demand vehicle categories and underperforming segments.</li>
        <li>Generate actionable insights to support marketing and product strategy.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üìä Tools & Techniques</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Python</li>
        <li>Pandas, NumPy for data manipulation</li>
        <li>Matplotlib, Seaborn for data visualization</li>
        <li>Jupyter Notebook for analysis and reporting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üìà Key Outcomes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Identified top-performing vehicle segments and their associated customer profiles.</li>
        <li>Visualized regional and demographic trends influencing purchase decisions.</li>
        <li>Provided strategic recommendations to align product offerings with market demand.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <p>This project strengthened my ability to translate raw data into meaningful business insights and laid the foundation for predictive modeling and data-driven decision making in future modules.</p>
